inbox.body:
Giving you the tools you need to make informed decisions

We’re excited to  announce our partnership with Garbo, a non-profit dedicated to empowering people to make more informed decisions about their safety. By providing background checks that are based on public records and reports that identify violence or abuse in a person’s past, Garbo’s mission is to help prevent gender-based violence online—and now Tinder is bringing that mission to more people.  

With features like Photo Verification to ensure the person you’re chatting with is the person in their photos and Noonlight, which gives you back up every time you meet someone IRL, your safety remains top of mind. 

Tinder is committed to developing products and building relationships that help maintain a safe space for people to connect on and off our platform. For resources and more information about our current safety features, please visit our  Safety Center.
